When drawing an ellipse with specific but not pathological values and a line thickness less than 5, horizontal lines are displayed.
The following snipped is sufficient to expose the problem:
![Screenshot from 2020-01-07 12-21-10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13381545/71895240-67606b80-3148-11ea-8f67-3b862e7f11b7.png)
```
#include <opencv2/viz/types.hpp>
#include <opencv2/imgproc/imgproc.hpp>
#include <opencv2/highgui.hpp> // for imshow

int main(int argc, char** argv){
  cv::RotatedRect rect;
  rect.angle = 6.52944;
  rect.center.x = 201.968;
  rect.center.y = 373.492;
  rect.size.width = 65.2557;
  rect.size.height = 20.5783;

  cv::Mat test(848,800,CV_8UC3);
  cv::ellipse(test,rect,cv::viz::Color::magenta(),2);
  cv::imshow("windowName", test);
  cv::waitKey(0);
}
```
When using a higher thickness (e.g., 5) the problem goes away.

