Hello!
Here I am to report an issue because it's impossible for me to figure out where is hidden my problem.
I am using a Logitech Quickam pro 9000 webcam and can't do any capture with.
Yet, I can't believe there is a problem with the camera installation because it greatly works with its own software "Logitech Webcam Software".
Moreover, openCV seems to be pretty well installed too, until I can import and process images or even videos with application built with opencv.
Finally, I am using a perfectly basic code you can find everywhere wich is :
```.cpp
#include "opencv2/core.hpp"
#include "opencv2/imgproc.hpp"
#include "opencv2/highgui/highgui.hpp"
#include "opencv2/videoio.hpp"
#include <iostream>

//using namespace cv;
//using namespace std;

int main() {

	cvNamedWindow("Raw", CV_WINDOW_NORMAL); 
	CvCapture* capture;
	IplImage * frame;
	char c;
	capture = cvCaptureFromCAM(0);  // works with 0 (ANY) or with an number between 10 and 19 included

	if (capture) {
		std::cout << "CAPTURE SUCCEEDED\n";
		while (1) {
			frame = cvQueryFrame(capture);
			if (!frame) {
				std::cout << "no frame\n";
				cvWaitKey(2000);
			}
			else {
				std::cout << "frame\n";
				("Raw", frame);
			}
			c = cvWaitKey(33);
			if (c == 27) break;
		}
	}
	else if (!capture)	std::cout << "NO CAPTURE\n";
	cvWaitKey(3000);
	cvReleaseCapture(&capture);
	cvDestroyWindow("Raw");
	return 0;
}```
When I use it, is written in my shell :"CAPTURE SUCCEEDED" and then "frame" several times.
So the connection to the camera seems to be good and the frame retrieving seems working too.
However, I capture nothing. The window "Raw" is totally grey, while the logitech controller opens well.
I tried the same with a Kinect for PC which works perfectly with its own software too : the same grey window while frames seem retrieved.
I also tried with OpenCV 2.4.10 and Visual Studio 2010 pro : always exactly the same result.
I've finally tried a few different methods of coding, using a videocapture object for example : not better.
I stared in the issues and answers categories of opencv, no one seems to have discussed of this problem of grey or black window before.
If anyone had an idea of the origin of the problem ... I would love him
Thank you !

