In Mat1b, behaviour of uchar divided by a number differs when:
1) working per pixel -> result is truncated
2) working with Mat1b directly -> result is rounded
```.cpp
#include "opencv2/opencv.hpp"
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
using namespace cv;

int main() {
    Mat1b m1(1,1), m2(1,1);
    m1<<3;
    m2<<3;

    m1/=4;
    m2[0][0]/=4;

    cout<<m1<<endl;
    cout<<m2<<endl;

    return 0;
}
```
Output:
```
[  1]
[  0]
```
Expected output:
```
[  0]
[  0]
```
answers.opencv.org, Stack Overflow, etc and have not found solution

